$TSLA $NIO $TM $LI $XPEV
As the market recovers, China’s sales of SUVs, minivans and sedans rose by double digits in November but were below pre-pandemic levels for the year.
Sales rose 11.6%Y/Y to 2.3M, according to the China Association of Automobile Manufacturers.
Total vehicle sales, including trucks and buses, rose 12.6% to 2.8M, holding steady at October’s growth rate.
Retail sales of cars, SUVs and multiple-purpose vehicles gained 7.8% Y/Y to 2.11M and wholesales of new energy vehicles, including electric cars, more than doubled to 169,000 units for the month. November sales of all-electric and gasoline-electric hybrid vehicles more than doubled, rising 104.9% Y/Y and YTD sales edged back above pre-virus levels with 3.9% Y/Y growth.YTD sales of heavy-duty trucks surged 39%  to 1.5M units.
Full-year auto sales are on track to decline for a third year after hitting a peak in 2017.
